==========================================================
Steps to build lib3 from scratch:

1) Make sure the correct version of ifort (or gfortran) is configured,
   e.g. linux: /opt/intel/fc/10.1.015/bin/ifortvars.sh
   e.g. macintel: /opt/intel/Compiler/11.1/076/bin/ifortvars.sh ia32

2) In a fresh directory, pull OCSSW.env and lib3 src dir from svn:

   svn export svn://svn0.domain.sdps/OCSSW/trunk/OCSSW.env
   svn co svn://svn0.domain.sdps/OCSSW/trunk/build/lib3/src
   mkdir install

3) Edit OCSSW.env:

   -set LIB3_DIR to the full path of a installation directory, e.g. ~/lib3/install
   -set compilers via the variables CC, CXX, and FC

4) Execute:

   export OCSSWROOT <ocssw_root_dir>  (parent of OCSSW build dir, e.g. ~/seadas/src)
   source OCSSW.env
   cd src
   ./BuildIt |& tee make.out

6) Check the make.out file for errors. Only errors should be:

   rm: cannot remove `src/libsdst.a': No such file or directory
   rm: cannot remove `lib/libsdst.a': No such file or directory
AND
   Error: Cannot write field "Vegetat"
   Field "Vegetat" has not been defined.


==========================================================
This is the order needed to compile the 3rd party libraries

jpeg
szip
gsl
hdf4
hdf5
hdfeos
hdfeos5
sdptk
sdst
mapi

We're currently compiling hdf4 without szip, but we may be using it with hdf5.

==========================================================
jpeg

setenv CFLAGS "-m64 -O3"
setenv F77 f77
setenv FFLAGS "-m64 -extend_source -convert big_endian -assume byterecl -save -O3"

==========================================================
gsl

setenv CFLAGS -m64
setenv F77 f77
setenv FFLAGS "-m64 -extend_source -convert big_endian -assume byterecl -save -O3"

==========================================================
hdf4

setenv CFLAGS "-m64 -O3"
setenv F77 f77
setenv FFLAGS "-m64 -extend_source -convert big_endian -assume byterecl -save -O3"

==========================================================
hdf5

setenv CFLAGS "-m64 -O3"
setenv F77 f77
setenv FFLAGS "-m64 -extend_source -convert big_endian -assume byterecl -save -O3"
setenv F9X 'f77'
setenv F9X 'f77 -fpp -DDEC$=DEC_ -DMS$=MS_'

==========================================================
hdfeos

setenv LINUX_BRAND linux64

==========================================================
hdfeos5

setenv LINUX_BRAND linux64

==========================================================
mapi

nothing

==========================================================
sdptk

setenv CC gcc
setenv F77 f77
setenv LINUX_BRAND linux64
#setenv LINUX_BRAND linux
setenv JPEGHOME /usr
setenv ZLIBHOME /usr
setenv SZIPHOME $HDFROOT

